Ads on Snapchat can be based on:\10• Your identity details and use of Snap services\10• Audience lists from advertisers and other partners\10• Your use of websites and apps that share activity with Snap\10\10You can customize the information used to serve you ads by going to Snapchat Settings → Additional Services: Manage → Ad Preferences.
Why am I seeing this ad?

Some ads on Snapchat are based on things you do elsewhere. You can disable receiving ads based on certain types of information, but you will still see ads. Also, ads may still be based on your use of Snap services.

Ads on Snapchat appear in various places, like Discover, Lenses, and Stories. Ads may be customized for you based on your activity in the app (like which content you watch), profile details (like your birthday), information from our ad partners, and other means. We\'ve created our ad products to be fun and engaging — we hope you like them!
